There is a chill to the air blowing in from the eastern wastes here, yet
the excitment of the bazaar with its tumult keeps the cold from your spirit
if not your body. The center of the bazaar overwhelms your senses with the
smell and sizzle of roast mutton, its cries of hawkers and cajoling
merchants. Jugglers, minstrels, and street dancers a-whirl to stay warm
amuse the crowds gathered near a large marble fountain.
