*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 5
You can read the name "Markan ConDion", engraved in gold lettering.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
You see a circular tower formed out of what appears to be a
single piece of deep red granite. The only opening you can reach
is a massive iron-bound oak gate. Over the gate is a large
bas-relief carving of an eagle in flight. Further up on the
walls you see several arrow slits and a balcony. From the
parapet hangs a pennant embroidered with the same eagle depicted
in the carving over the gate. A bronze plaque is mounted to the
tower wall next to the gate.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 6
You take an involuntary step back as you gaze closely at the
carving. Its fine detail and immense size make it look ready to
launch itself from the tower wall into battle. In its talons,
the eagle is carrying a large claidhmore engraved with its own
likeness across the length of the blade. As you move to inspect
the carving from another angle, the eagle's eyes seem to follow
you without ever moving.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH 6
  IFVAR ORG = 6
    ECHO ALL Suddenly, the eagle comes to life and raises its wings in salute.
    ECHO ALL The eagle settles back down and returns to its lifeless state.
  ELSE
    IFVAR ALIGN < -5
      ECHO OTHERS The eagle suddenly comes to life, and shrieks off into the sky.
      DAMAGEPLR SLASH 20 The eagle animates under your touch, and vaults itself into the sky, only to swoop down upon you and slash you with its claws.
      ECHO OTHERS The eagle swoops down and slashes %n with its claws.
      ECHO ALL The eagle comes to a rest over the gate, and returns to its lifeless state.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
