NUMBER 375
NAME Palace, grounds
MONSTER_GROUP 15
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Bright flowers flourish under the trees which line the sanded path leading
from the gate to the formal entrance of the Royal Palace. One could spend
hours admiring the work of the Royal Gardener who tends these grounds. The
palace itself stands witness to another artisan at the top of his profession.
Broad steps of blue marble lead to a series of fluted marble pillars, which
with their entablature, are sculpted to look like nymphs. Ivy in urns between
the pillars embrace the nymphs in chaste leaves. A functionary pauses in the
entryway, tapping his finger against a tablet in his hands, then continues on.
A gate leads back to the city.
*DESCRIPTION_END
